# Copyright and File Headers

## C++ (`.hpp`, `.cpp`, `.ixx`, etc.)

**REQUIRED**: Start every C++ translation unit and header with a Doxygen file block:

```cpp
/**
 * @file relative/path/to/file.hpp
 * @brief Short description of the file’s purpose.
 * @copyright Copyright (c) YYYY Boyle Development Team
 */
```

- Replace `YYYY` with the year of creation or last substantial edit, per team policy.
- Keep **exactly one blank line** after the closing `*/` before includes or pragma.

## Python (`.py`, `.pyi`)

Use a single-line header:

```python
# Copyright (c) YYYY Boyle Development Team. All rights reserved.
```

## Exemptions

- **`CMakeLists.txt` and `*.cmake`**: no Doxygen copyright block (CMake lists first).
- **`.mdc` Cursor rules**: YAML frontmatter **must** be line 1; do not prepend a copyright block.

## License

Project license: **BSD 3-Clause**. Do not paste full license text into every file unless project policy changes.
